&gt; Extended characters in identifiers may now be specified directly in the input encoding (UTF-8, by default), in addition to the UCN syntax (\uNNNN or \UNNNNNNNN) that is already supported:<p><pre><code>    static const int p = 3;
    int get_naïve_pi() {
      return p;
    }
</code></pre>
Lovely!
